description:
Brian lives in Waterville, Maine, with his wife and fellow artist Amy K. Cyrway. He currently works as a full-time graphic designer, freelance illustrator, and web developer. His best-known comic creations revolve around a trio of flaunting female characters, Bluette, Celest and Centura, created in the mid 90s. "Bluette's House", or just "Bluette" are the unofficial names of this entity.

Brian's portfolio consists of Heavy Metal Magazine, January 2010 and July, 2011; GASP Horror Magazine, and several novel covers for Sabledrake Publishing and Renaissance Alliance Publishing. In 2011 he was commissioned by actress Claudia Christian for her 2011 ClaudiaCon. Some of Brian's more popular works on the Internet include "Princess Pussy Bullet", the post-apocalyptic Bluette picture called "The Bitch and Her Dogs", and his rendition of Magic the Gathering's Akroma Angel of Wrath. Creative fans of the game continue to borrow this image for their own custom cards.
name: Brian Vigue
